In order for Monaco Editor to support typescript, we probably need to write our own bundler for .d.ts file.
ESBuild somehow refuse to bundle .d.ts file.
How to write your own bundler in just 100 lines of code: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Gc9-7PBqOC8

Tailwind CDN: https://cdn.tailwindcss.com?plugins=forms,typography,aspect-ratio
Check out how to implement Tailwind JIT: https://github.com/beyondcode/tailwindcss-jit-cdn

Fix strange TS typing: https://github.com/gxmari007/vite-plugin-eslint/pull/60/files#diff-8b4a10961bf384b8ef4355cd5867d07a675d6194ec644352b026facfc9b4f14e
